@hitthejohn   Sorry this puzzle didn’t do it for you.  One think that might help is to consider that the “?” can signal a play on words or some misdirection, not always a pun.  “Gives a hand” most commonly means “helps”.  But with the question mark, the playful answer becomes “CLAPS”.  That kind of cleverness made me smile.  

This was very similar to 36A:  “Preserves thing?” was not the action one might have thought without a question mark. The play-on-words answer is JARS.   I initially put in JAMS, but corrected with the cross.  Still a good clue/answer. 

For me it was fun and well done Sunday puzzle.
